records.nl_statement: Let $\mathbf{x}_1, \mathbf{x}_2, \ldots$ be a sequence of the points of the product space $\prod X_\alpha$.  Show that this sequence converges to the point $\mathbf{x}$ if and only if the sequence $\pi_\alpha(\mathbf{x}_i)$ converges to $\pi_\alpha(\mathbf{x})$ for each $\alpha$.

import Mathlib

open Filter Set TopologicalSpace

  (h : ∀ i, x i ∈ p i)
  (h' : ∀ i, y ∈ p i) :
  Tendsto x atTop (𝓝 y) ↔ ∀ i, Tendsto (λ j => x j) atTop (𝓝 y) := by sorry
